name: Microservices Architecture Template
description: A comprehensive template for building microservices-based applications with Kubernetes orchestration, Docker containers, and modern CI/CD practices. Includes service discovery, load balancing, and monitoring setup.

name: Monolithic Web Application Template
architecture: Traditional monolithic web application with MVC pattern
description: A template for building traditional monolithic web applications using the Model-View-Controller pattern. Includes user authentication, database integration, and RESTful API endpoints.

name: Serverless Functions Template
architecture: Serverless architecture with AWS Lambda and API Gateway
description: A template for building serverless applications using AWS Lambda functions, API Gateway, and other AWS services. Includes event-driven architecture and auto-scaling capabilities.

name: Event-Driven Architecture Template
architecture: Event-driven architecture with message queues and event sourcing
description: A template for building event-driven applications using message queues, event sourcing, and CQRS patterns. Includes Apache Kafka integration and event store setup.

name: Mobile Backend Template
architecture: Mobile backend with REST APIs and push notifications
description: A template for building mobile application backends with RESTful APIs, push notification services, and mobile-specific features like user management and content delivery.

name: Legacy PHP Template
architecture: Traditional PHP application with Apache and MySQL
description: Legacy template for PHP applications using Apache web server and MySQL database. This template is deprecated and should not be used for new projects.

name: Data Pipeline Template
architecture: Data processing pipeline with ETL and analytics
description: A template for building data processing pipelines with ETL processes, data warehousing, and analytics capabilities. Includes Apache Spark, Kafka, and visualization tools.

name: IoT Platform Template
architecture: Internet of Things platform with device management
description: A template for building IoT platforms with device management, real-time data processing, and dashboard visualization. Includes MQTT protocol support and edge computing capabilities.
